      "name": "Dumetella",
      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "The grey catbird — a monotypic genus of medium-sized, slate-grey songbird named for its distinctive mewing call that sounds like a cat. Despite its subdued colouration, it is a gifted mimic, often incorporating the songs of other birds into its own rambling, discontinuous song.",
